== Laws of the Kingdom of Cetha ==


Admittance to Southport

    1. To enter, you are not permitted to wear a helmet or hood or use any other method to conceal your identity. Head coverings may be worn after entrance is permitted.
    2. Weapons may be carried or sheathed in city limits, provided weapons are only used in self-defense or at the direction of local law enforcement.
    3. Kingdom personnel may stop you to verify your identity against banishment lists.
    --> 3. 1. Failure to comply with requests from official personnel will result in violation of Criminal Law, point 4.

----------------------------------------


Banishment from Southport

    The following creatures are banished and will be killed on sight:
        - Orcs
        - Drow
        - Trolls
        - Orogs
        - Undead
        - Yuan-Ti
        - Ogrillons
        - Lizardfolk
        - Goblinoids
        - Full-blooded Fiends
        - Gnolls

    1. Individuals listed on the Kingdom's separate banishment list will not be permitted entry.
    2. Only the Magistrate or royal family of Cetha may approve permanent banishment of individuals.
    3. Temporary banishment of 24 hours may be given by guards and official personnel of the Kingdom of Cetha.
    4. Individuals who have been banished have the right to request an appeal. Appeals will be observed by the Magistrate of Law.

----------------------------------------


Criminal Law

    1. Murder and Manslaughter.
    2. Assault.
    3. Thievery, Banditry, and Slavery.
    4. Disturbing the Public Safety and Peace.
    5. Harassment.
    6. Bribery, Extortion, and Blackmail.
    7. Public Indecency.
    8. Vandalism to Public or Private Property.


Spellcasting Law

    1. The casting of offensive spells is prohibited, except in defense of self or others, or for training purposes overseen by Kingdom personnel.
    2. Casting of defensive spells is permitted.
    3. Shapeshifting, either through magic or innate ability, into creatures listed on the banished lists is prohibited.
    --> 3. 1. The shapeshifting individual will be killed on sight.
    4. Summoned creatures may travel with their summoner.
    --> 4. 1. Summoned creatures that infringe on Criminal Law point 4 are prohibited, as determined by guard and official Kingdom personnel.
    --> 4. 2. Summoned creatures that are listed on the banished lists are prohibited and will be killed on sight.
    --> 4. 3. The summoner is responsible for all actions of the summoned creature, including any criminal actions.

This is the default waypoint you may place to set a patrol path for a creature or NPC.
1. Create the creature and either use its current Tag or fill in a new one.
2. Place or make sure the WalkWayPoints() is within the body of the On Spawn script for the creature.
3. Place a series of waypoints along the route you wish the creature to walk.
4. Select all of the newly created waypoints and right click. Choose the Create Set option.
5. The waypoint set will have a set name of "WP_" + NPC Tag. Thus if an NPC with the Tag "Guard" will have a waypoint set called "WP_Guard". Note that Tags are case sensitive.
